In addition to the categories of third parties identified above, we may have disclosed personal information about you to government entities for the purposes listed in our Privacy Policy, or to third parties in connection with corporate transactions, such as mergers, acquisitions or divestitures during the 12-month period before the Last Updated date of this California Notice.
California Consumer Privacy Rights
Please see the “Exercising Your Rights” section of our US Notice and Section 8 (Your Rights) of the Depop Privacy Policy for information about your privacy rights and how to exercise them.
Shine the Light
California residents are entitled to ask for a notice describing what categories of personal information we disclose to third parties for their own direct marketing purposes. Depop does not disclose any personal information to third parties for their own direct marketing purposes, unless you otherwise consent to it.
If you have questions about these practices, or would like to make a request, you can contact us
at
data@depop.com
via our Help Centre
here
. In your request, please include the statement “Shine the Light Request," and provide your first and last name and mailing address and certify that you are a California resident. We may need additional information to confirm your identity and that you are resident in California. Please note that we will not accept requests via telephone, mail, or fax, and we are not responsible for notices that are not labelled or sent properly, or that do not have complete information.
Colorado Privacy Notice
This is our Colorado Notice. Please read it if you live in Colorado to find out more about  what we do with your data. Let us know if you need help in understanding what it means for you.
This Colorado Privacy Notice (
Colorado Notice
) supplements Depop’s US Notice and applies to personal information Depop collects online about Colorado consumers. We adopt this Colorado Notice to comply with the Colorado Privacy Act (the
CPA
). This Colorado Notice uses certain terms that have the meanings given to them in the CPA.
Collection and Use of Personal Information
We collect information about you when you use Depop, We have included more information about the data we collect below.
Please see Sections 1 (What data do we collect and how do we use it?) of the Depop Privacy Policy for information about the categories of personal information we collect and the purposes for which we use the information.
We use personal information for our business and commercial purposes, as described throughout the Depop Privacy Policy for the following purposes: providing the Service; processing orders and transactions; internal business analytics; tailoring and personalizing the Service to you; for advertising and marketing purposes; undertaking activities to verify or maintain the quality, integrity, and safety of our Service (and to improve, upgrade, or enhance them); maintaining or servicing accounts; providing customer service; verifying customer information; processing payments; and providing analytics services.
We do not knowingly process personal information from children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly process “sensitive data” as that term is defined under the CPA.
Sharing of Personal Information
We may need to share your data, for example with other companies that are in our group of companies, or to third parties that provide us with services or for legal reasons.
We share your information with our service providers or other third parties where necessary to perform the Services, comply with our legal obligations, or for purposes set out in this Privacy Policy. Your personal information will be shared with our service providers or other third parties
as described in more detail in Section 5 (Who do we share your data with?) of the Depop Privacy Policy
. The following table lists the categories of personal information and categories of service providers and third parties with whom we may share your information.
Please note that not every one of the following categories may apply to your personal information.
Categories of Personal Information
Categories of Third Parties With Whom We Share Personal Information
●  Buyer Account Information
●  Seller Account Information
●  Payments Information
●  Transaction Information
●  Customer Support Information
●  Survey Responses
●  Browser/Device Information
